# Changelog

## [Unreleased]

## [0.23.0] - 2025-11-05

### Added
- folders: comprehensive file-browser-like folder system for organizing series
  - tree structure with drag and drop support
  - multi-series selection, cut, copy, paste
  - folder creation, rename, deletion with confirmation
  - series filtering within folders
  - unclassified series management
  - batch operations with horizon selector
  - links to tsinfo, quickview, tseditor per folder
- ui/tsinfo: dependents tab showing series that depend on current one
- ui/tsinfo: folder path display and editing
- quickview: download as csv button with datetime suffix
- q-editor: by.at-path and by.without-path operators implementation
- q-editor: links from basket to quickview
- q-editor: clickable basket list with cursor indicators
- stat-info: quality indicator for inferred frequency
- stat: standard deviation calculation
- time localization for date display according to horizon settings

### Changed
- tseditor: refined model of series with improved data handling
- tseditor: better handling of editable cells in outer-merge situations
- tseditor: scalar type forcing for empty strings
- tseditor: extraction and testing of merge and patch functions
- tsinfo: formula operators now link to basket editor (by.basket)
- tsinfo: localized insertion dates in history and time-travel
- quickview: plot height now fraction of viewport
- quickview: improved layout with download button under plot
- folders: extensive UX improvements with better styling, error handling, loading states
- menu: display changes trigger resize event

### Fixed
- tseditor: saving data for naive series in basket/query mode
- tseditor: fillNas handling for missing values
- tseditor: menu fold/unfold behavior
- quickview: instanciation by query
- quickview: browser stored horizon loading
- q-editor: page instanciation via permalink
- folders: consistency between cut and drop actions
- folders: various edge cases and error handling

## [0.22.0] - 2025-08-29

### Added
- ui/groups: horizon widget for group pages
- ui/horizon: canadian timezone support
- query editor:
  - basic and expert search modes with tabs
  - filter tree operations (expand, simplify, delete)
  - drag and drop support for filter nodes
  - grab cursor for list items
  - filter for basket names in baskets list
  - root "and" expression initialization in expert mode
  - conversion from basic to expert filter on first switch
- tseditor multi-series editing:
  - 2d table support for editing multiple series simultaneously
  - rectangular selection and copy/paste
  - cell-level edition mode
  - arrow key navigation (left/right) in 2d table
  - typing triggers cell activation (standard spreadsheet behavior)
  - improved ctrl key behavior
  - rounded values display in non-editing cells
  - proper focus management outside edition table
  - dates and column headers integrated into coorddata model
  - focusable and selectable dates with visual feedback
  - copy dates without overwriting functionality
  - back button in creation edit mode
  - show/hide current diff toggle
  - protection for non-editable columns from erasure
  - display of falsy inputs (0, false, etc.)
  - improved selection boundaries visualization
- custom paste method using div wrapper instead of input element tweaking
- schema: horizon default values initialization

### Changed
- search ui:
  - aerated text input fields
  - cache interface tweaks
  - source and metadata display in export mode
  - avoid wrapping bynames in redundant "and" clauses
- tseditor refactoring:
  - selection info moved to model root instead of data
  - components data properly organized
  - better zoom handling for multi-series
  - restore cancel action functionality
  - delete cell on focus with "del" key
  - coorddata now includes dates (column -1) and headers
  - improved diff table display and styling
  - primary edition view behavior restored
  - creation from scratch behavior restored
  - better na representation (not shown as deletion)
- folders ui:
  - restrict to local series only (federation read-only in future)
  - improved click zones for folder open/close
  - replaced popover with css solution for better elm integration
  - better error state display and loading indicators
  - queue count display for pending operations
  - style homogenization with rest of ui
- test/web: updated for metadata integrity changes (removed tablename field)

### Fixed
- ui/groupinfo: removed inferfreq button for groups (not supported)
- tseditor:
  - ensure non-editable cells cannot be altered by key presses
  - clean current diff when necessary
  - proper fill setup placement
  - falsy input display
  - non-editable column protection
  - na representation distinct from deletion
  - focus error tracking
- folders:
  - server update after failed series displacement
  - error counting in transactions
  - browser resource limits with large batch operations (>1300 series)

## [0.21.0] - 2025-02-25

### Added
- tseditor enhancements:
  - series creation mode with form validation
  - statistical indicators display (mean, std, min, max, count, nas)
  - inferred frequency calculation with unlock mechanism
  - linear transformation for edited values
  - multi-cell selection with mouse drag and keyboard shortcuts
  - copy/paste for dates and values separately
  - fill nas functionality with buttons
  - thousands separator formatting for display
  - round values feature with +/- buttons and local storage
  - show all points button for large datasets
  - cancel edition button
  - keyboard navigation with arrow keys, page up/down
  - shift+click for range selection, ctrl+shift+arrow for select to limits
- groupinfo page improvements:
  - rename mechanism (commented out pending integrity guarantees)
  - copy icon next to group name
  - user metadata in dedicated tab
  - error message for non-existent groups
  - log entries for primary groups
- query editor:
  - addressable with ?basket=<basket-name> parameter
  - proposals for metadata keys, sources, and cache policies
  - "by.and" operator selected by default for new baskets
- formula editor:
  - loading indicator during plot rendering
  - create/update indication when saving formulas
- monitoring:
  - /ping endpoint for health checks
- configuration:
  - new configuration object usage
  - dashboard link configuration
- vertical zoom support in tsinfo page

### Changed
- tseditor refactoring:
  - unified series model with naked and toedit modes
  - edition type system (edition string | noedition | deletion)
  - better handling of nas groups with start position tracking
  - improved paste behavior after horizon actions
  - deselect cells on save and escape key
  - lose focus on horizon interaction
  - permalink moved to header
  - compact table header and vertical space optimization
- horizon widget:
  - better zoom behavior preserving non-updated components
  - timezone choices in model
  - debug view showing zoomy values
- groupinfo:
  - moved delete button to right
  - fixed cache button for formula groups
  - avoid boundformula requests for non-bound groups
- tsinfo:
  - removed cache button for primaries
  - unified getidates function
  - always expect non-cached idates to avoid conflicts
- plot improvements:
  - removed "editor.code" title
  - more generous margins to avoid truncations
  - default axis with hoverformat set to "locals"
- configuration and setup:
  - removed cli module (now useless)
  - schema registration at init-db time
  - integration with refinery architecture
  - switch postgresql port to 5434 for server usage

### Fixed
- tseditor:
  - spurious /supervision calls for formulas
  - horizon interaction bugs
  - deletion cleanup for raw field
  - thousands separator on integers
  - focus persistence after copy
  - nas position calculation after zoom
  - negative number parsing (-123.45)
  - interval metadata closing right bounds
  - paste data space removal
  - formula components using correct api endpoint
- plot rendering for edited values during editing
- query editor "by.source" input help
- config file handling for missing dashboard section
- werkzeug version constraint (< 3.1.x)
- metadata decoder for null intervals
- test adjustments for upstream changes

### Removed
- cache: spurious h1 title
- cli module completely
- duplicated and unused functions in ui modules

## [0.20.1] - 2024-10-25

### Fixed
- packaging: include missing schema.sql resource file

## [0.20.0] - 2024-10-22

### Added
- quickview page with y-axis zoom support:
  - persistent y-zoom parameters in url
  - synchronized y-zoom across tsinfo and tseditor views
  - legend selection state tracking from plotly
- pro feature detection:
  - automatic hiding of pro-only menu items when refinery_pro not available
  - /ispro endpoint check for conditional menu rendering
- horizon widget enhancements:
  - better date format validation (date vs datetime)
  - improved json key naming between client and server
- tsinfo history improvements:
  - user-configurable max revisions display
  - navigation arrows for stepping through insertion dates one by one
  - better handling of last N versions instead of first N
  - idate displayed as html element with css styling
  - automatic history reset on horizon changes
- settings backend improvements:
  - configurationerror for bad configuration
  - proper 500 error handling with detailed messages

### Changed
- tseditor optimizations:
  - zoom preservation after editing
  - renamed editedts to zoomedts for clarity
  - skip insertion-dates query for formulas
  - monotonic index generation instead of random
  - formula components loaded after main series
  - better handling of edited values during zoom
- horizon widget:
  - renamed newdates to datesfromzoom
  - zoombounds now nothing instead of ["", ""] when empty
  - aligned horizonbounds with other bound types
- tsinfo cache improvements:
  - cache parameter now affects version requests
  - cache toggle wipes and replaces insertion dates
- query improvements:
  - editor links only use zoombounds in query
  - better bounds formalism using maybe (string, string)
  - optimized full history requests

### Fixed
- tseditor zoom conservation and change behavior
- horizon empty bounds handling
- tsinfo roundtrip zoom preservation with horizon actions
- proper error propagation from backend to web client
- user metadata migration with mandatory parameters
- settings validation robustness

### Removed
- graph title display of idate (moved to html element)
- redundant code in history view paths

## [0.19.0] - 2024-08-22

### Added
- new elm-based time series editor (tseditor) with:
  - table display of series values with editing capabilities
  - excel copy/paste support
  - timezone selection (utc/cet)
  - inferred frequency option to detect gaps
  - synchronization between graph zoom and table display
  - cache control for formula series
  - override highlighting for edited values
- time horizon widget with:
  - predefined periods (2 weeks, 1 month, 3 months, 1 year, all)
  - navigation arrows for time offset
  - local storage persistence
  - date bounds display
- history mode for visualizing series evolution:
  - interactive timeline slider
  - color-coded historical curves
  - point evolution tracking on hover
  - limited to 70 insertion dates for performance
- query editor (qeditor) for basket management:
  - filter tree visualization
  - basket creation and editing
  - lisp expression parsing
- standalone menu system:
  - icon and text modes
  - current page highlighting
  - consistent navigation across all views
- new homepage replacing cockpit
- operators page with syntax highlighting
- formula batch ui
- security roles support (admin, rw, ro, guest)

### Changed
- completely rewrote tseditor replacing dash-based version
- migrated all views to use standalone menu system
- improved tsinfo with:
  - tabbed interface for different aspects
  - metadata badges on series name line
  - formula depth slider improvements
  - better delete/rename action placement
- enhanced formula editor with:
  - text mode editing
  - better validation
  - void type handling
  - support for ** operator
- upgraded elm tooling and dependencies
- simplified data fetching with keepnans parameter
- better css organization and naming conventions

### Fixed
- horizon widget offset buttons when series out of bounds
- table jumping on save button appearance
- plotly rendering timing issues with tabs
- negative number handling in editor
- paste action reliability
- timezone display for naive series
- insertion date checking for concurrent edits
- many style and layout improvements

### Removed
- old dash-based history module
- elm-integrated menu system (replaced with standalone)
- redundant cdn links
- unused model items and code

